commitmsg: Use named sources when loading tests
strip route namespaces, which different per Junos version
give progress indication while downloading policies
better fix: only elt.find() can return None

dump and load JSON instead of pickles

Fixes #1.
traffic from unoccupied per-host IPs is permitted
intra-AWS flows are governed both by incoming and outgoing rules
correctly translate any to all apps

cache connections per region

Without this, only the first region was analyzed

Refactor AWS processing to get all SG's first

This allows a smoother process, and more importantly collects all of the
known apps before generating any rules.

Attempt to translate */any to all apps

This isn't quite right, because the list of apps may grow over time, so
there's more to do for #8.

Process AWS egress rules, too

Without this, no egress traffic is allowed.  Fixes #12.

add tests for fwunit.ip

More tests for #9.

This also tries to make IPPairs a bit more efficient for reading,
possibly at the expense of writing.  And still doesn't achieve
normalization.  Harrumph.

add tests for combine

By no means complete, but giving me a better confidence that I've got
them right - see #9.

Add a 'combine' policy type

This combines rules from multiple policy sets, each associated with an
IP space they are responsible for

Introduce application maps

This allows the per-policy-type application names to be mapped to a
common set of names to simplify tests.  Fixes #5.

Switch to a single 'fwunit' script, with config

This fixes #6.

Handle SG's pointing to other SG's

Closes #4.

Read AWS configuration and produce rules

closes #7

refactor to parse rules from other sources

spoiler alert: Amazon S3 Security Groups!
include "any -> any: any" rules for traffic within each attached network
more support that became necessary as tests were added
set up for actually running unit tests
I'm a grow'd up package now
complete parsing into denormalized rule set

Always handle rules as dicts keyed by app

In most cases, this is the useful form.  And in particular for tests
that address only one app (the most common kind), this allows much
quicker access to the relevant rules.
Bug 1081920: Correctly handle the 'any-ipv6' *address*, not app

Ignore app 'any-ipv6'

This is a built-in application like 'any', but for IPv6, which fwunit
doesn't support.
update to use Rules by source name, rather than path
make test_parse_zones not depend on nondeterministic object ordering
